  "body": "## ISSUE 1: Nickname overlaps the display name\r\n\r\n### Steps:\r\n1. `User A` sets a nickname for `User B`\r\n2. `User A` checks the following places\r\n3. `User B` sends a message to `User A`\r\n4. `User A` checks in the following places:\r\n  - In first line of message\r\n  - In the chat preview\r\n  - Contacts tab\r\n  - 'new chat' overlay\r\n\r\n### Actual result: \r\nNickname overlaps the display name in the following places:\r\n-  In first line of message\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/5538faa1-7c2d-47ca-b384-f2a8a96134e1)\r\n-  In the chat preview![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/3991a687-9e37-4017-bc3b-77c68960342a)\r\n- Contacts tab\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/b09c807f-f8a2-4b6b-830e-3ce5a72e0034)\r\n- 'new chat' overlay\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/2929eb07-33bc-4a1c-95e4-a8de1114f0bc)\r\n\r\n### Expected result: \r\nThe display name should be shown in the right part after the nickname.\r\n![image](https://github.com/status-im/status-mobile/assets/52490791/04a1211a-9c12-4ef1-8f5a-b9964f165e0d)\r\n",
